556
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,200
What holiday?

557
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:54,900
It's a harvest thing,
family coming from out of town.

558
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:56,600
- Okay, Saturday.
MACON: - Lena!

559
00:37:56,700 --> 00:37:59,400
- I don't know, hurry up.
- Say yes.

560
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:01,000
Yes.

561
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:03,400
Can I see you tomorrow?

562
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:06,900
- I don't know. Get out of here.
- Okay.

563
00:38:09,800 --> 00:38:11,100
(CHUCKLES)

564
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:14,500
LENA: Ethan?

565
00:38:14,700 --> 00:38:15,900
Yeah?

566
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:20,000
Promise me it'll be a really normal,
awkward teenager date.

567
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:22,200
I swear. I won't even call you after.

568
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:24,800
- Jerk.
- Witch.

569
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:27,000
- Jock.
- Heh.

570
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:30,700
See you tomorrow.

571
00:38:33,900 --> 00:38:36,400
You could have made a ladder, you know.

572
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:49,400
Keep your distance.

573
00:39:51,700 --> 00:39:56,000
MACON: Thank you kindly
for your courteous welcome.

574
00:39:56,900 --> 00:39:59,000
I felt something tonight.

575
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:02,100
Been feeling something every night
since you brought that girl.

576
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:05,000
It's the only place left I have to protect her.

577
00:40:05,200 --> 00:40:07,800
So you bring darkness to this town.

578
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:11,900
I can feel it like a hand twisting my insides.

579
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:13,300
Well, that's not Lena.

580
00:40:14,900 --> 00:40:16,500
Sarafine?

581
00:40:17,500 --> 00:40:19,400
You said she was gone for good.

582
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:24,400
Yeah. Well, we...
We did have an agreement, but...

583
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:28,400
...she's been shadowing Lena
for the past year.

584
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:31,300
And there have been some accidents.

585
00:40:31,500 --> 00:40:34,900
Macon, no danger better come
to that boy because of your kind.

586
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:37,500
Yeah, well, then, you Keep him on a leash.

587
00:40:38,400 --> 00:40:41,300
- What happened at Greenbrier?
- I don't know.

588
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,900
Lena was hysterical.

589
00:40:43,100 --> 00:40:46,100
Boy was unconscious.
I brought him home, called you.

590
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:48,600
You're the seer, you tell me what happened.

591
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:52,300
This is the sacred place of my ancestors.
You hear?

592
00:40:52,500 --> 00:40:54,700
You want some answers,
you show me some respect.

593
00:40:54,900 --> 00:40:57,900
Yeah, I... I apologize.

594
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:03,400
Ethan had some kind of charm.
It had a Duchannes power in it.

595
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:05,600
Well, that would be Sarafine.

596
00:41:06,300 --> 00:41:10,000
Maybe she's using the charm
to get to Lena through the boy.

597
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:12,700
You tell them I have to know
what Sarafine's up to.

598
00:41:12,900 --> 00:41:16,100
It wouldn't break your face to ask
for help instead of expecting it.

599
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:19,900
Like your family's been doing for too
many years. Don't roll your eyes at me.

600
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:25,300
Then please ask them kindly
what Sarafine is up to.

601
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:28,700
Brought your favorites, Uncle Abner.

602
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:31,200
Shrimp and grits.

603
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:33,700
Fried oysters.

604
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:37,200
And a coconut pie.

605
00:41:37,400 --> 00:41:40,200
Hmm. No wonder he's no longer with us.

606
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:42,900
Pay no attention to him, uncle.

607
00:41:53,900 --> 00:41:58,200
Uncle Abner,
we are in need of your intercession.

608
00:41:58,700 --> 00:42:01,200
Along with Aunt Ida and Auntie May...

609
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:04,600
...I humbly call upon your spirits.

610
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,400
What are they saying?

611
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:19,700
Nothing. Nothing yet.

612
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:23,500
Tell them they have to help us stop Sarafine.

613
00:42:26,100 --> 00:42:28,500
Somethings cannot be stopped.

614
00:42:45,300 --> 00:42:47,300
(SIREN WAILING)

615
00:43:30,500 --> 00:43:33,900
LENA: - This is your favorite spot?
ETHAN: - It's all about the sign.

616
00:43:34,100 --> 00:43:36,700
- You see up there?
- Mm-hm.

617
00:43:36,900 --> 00:43:38,900
That's the road to freedom, heh.

618
00:43:39,400 --> 00:43:42,400
My mama used to say,
"Get out of this town as soon as you can.

619
00:43:42,600 --> 00:43:47,700
Go find out how other people live and think
before you find a place that's yours."

620
00:43:47,900 --> 00:43:52,400
And I'd say, "Mom, I'm 9. How do I do that?"

621
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:54,200
Little Ethan.

622
00:43:54,400 --> 00:43:55,800
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

623
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:58,600
So that's when she took me to the library.

624
00:43:58,800 --> 00:44:01,900
And, um, she said:

625
00:44:02,100 --> 00:44:04,300
"Ethan, this is my church.

626
00:44:04,400 --> 00:44:08,900
This is where my family goes
to celebrate what's holy:

627
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:10,800
Ideas."

628
00:44:12,300 --> 00:44:15,100
Oh, wow, sorry. Ha, ha.

629
00:44:15,300 --> 00:44:17,600
Don't know where that came from.

630
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:19,100
(SIGHS)

631
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:23,000
I wish I'd known her.

632
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:27,600
Let's get out of here. Let's go.

633
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:29,600
- Where?
- Anywhere.

634
00:44:30,700 --> 00:44:34,600
Lena, most people spend their entire lives...

635
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,700
...waiting for a moment that's gonna change
everything. It never happens.

636
00:44:38,900 --> 00:44:41,500
We can start our lives right now, okay?

637
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:45,900
We just gotta say yes,
we just gotta get in the car, and just go.

638
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,300
- I can't do that.
- Why?

639
00:44:50,500 --> 00:44:55,400
When I turn 16, I might not even be
who I am now.

640
00:44:55,900 --> 00:44:57,500
Why? What...?

641
00:44:57,700 --> 00:45:00,500
What could happen
besides getting your first hangover?

642
00:45:00,700 --> 00:45:02,000
(CHUCKLES)

643
00:45:05,500 --> 00:45:10,200
When a female Caster turns 16,
we face what they call the Claiming.

644
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:14,200
My powers will be claimed
for either the Light or the Dark...

645
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:17,100
...depending on my true nature.

646
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:20,200
Whatever I'm destined to be.

647
00:45:20,700 --> 00:45:23,500
That's... That's why Macon brought me here.

648
00:45:23,700 --> 00:45:25,600
Wait, what's Macon?

649
00:45:25,700 --> 00:45:29,600
He's a Dark Caster, but he's choosing
to be Light for me now.

650
00:45:30,100 --> 00:45:32,200
He can choose? Then why can't you?

651
00:45:32,400 --> 00:45:37,300
They say that a female Caster's
true nature chooses for her.

652
00:45:38,100 --> 00:45:40,200
I don't know why.

653
00:45:40,700 --> 00:45:42,200
Back up, wait a minute.

654
00:45:42,300 --> 00:45:46,800
You're worried that when you turn 16,
you're gonna be an evil...

655
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:49,800
...bitch... Witch Caster?

656
00:45:49,900 --> 00:45:52,400
I have 75 days left, Ethan.

657
00:45:56,300 --> 00:45:58,400
I don't know what I'll be.

658
00:46:00,500 --> 00:46:03,300
I don't know who I really am inside.

659
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:09,500
Now, in the last year, Lena Duchannes
has been in three different schools...

660
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:10,900
...in three different towns.

661
00:46:11,100 --> 00:46:15,400
I checked. And in every single one
of them schools, they had accidents...

662
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:18,100
...they had unnatural weather, they had...

663
00:46:18,300 --> 00:46:19,800
Well, they even had deaths.

664
00:46:19,900 --> 00:46:21,500
(MURMURING)

665
00:46:21,600 --> 00:46:23,900
Now, I have a petition here...

666
00:46:24,100 --> 00:46:27,900
...signed by over 300 Gatlin parents
who demand...

667
00:46:28,100 --> 00:46:30,600
- Demand that Lena Duchannes be expelled...
MACON: - Excuse me.

668
00:46:30,600 --> 00:46:32,500
...and furthermore that
the Ravenwood property...

669
00:46:32,700 --> 00:46:34,200
Excuse me.

670
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:35,900
(MURMURING)

671
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:43,200
Oh, my God, Mama...

672
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:47,100
Excuse me for my untimely intervention.

673
00:46:48,900 --> 00:46:50,900
Principal Herbert.

674
00:46:51,900 --> 00:46:53,400
Mayor Snow.

675
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:56,300
And the Reverend Stephens, I believe.

676
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,900
- Yes, sir.
- Hmm.

677
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:03,000
Mrs. Lincoln.

678
00:47:03,600 --> 00:47:07,600
How dare you enter the house of the Lord?

679
00:47:07,700 --> 00:47:10,700
Since my family own the land it's built on.

680
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:15,900
And I understood this to be an occasion
for all members of the community.

681
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:21,100
Now, I'm sure y'all have better things
to do on such a beautiful day...

682
00:47:21,300 --> 00:47:23,400
...so I'll be brief.

683
00:47:23,600 --> 00:47:28,400
The accusations against my niece
are all spurious lies.

684
00:47:28,600 --> 00:47:33,700
For, according to the Weather Channel,
and you can verify this on Google...

685
00:47:33,900 --> 00:47:37,100
...there were unseasonably
strong gusts from the east...

686
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:42,100
...which caused untold destruction
up and down the South Carolina coast.

687
00:47:42,300 --> 00:47:46,800
So my niece will go back to the institution...

688
00:47:46,900 --> 00:47:49,100
...that Gatlin presumes to call educational.

689
00:47:49,300 --> 00:47:51,900
And she will be persecuted no longer.

690
00:47:52,800 --> 00:47:56,200
I thank you all for your cooperation.

691
00:47:57,700 --> 00:48:00,600
MRS. LINCOLN:
You have no right to tell us what to do.

692
00:48:00,800 --> 00:48:03,300
No matter how much money you have.

693
00:48:03,500 --> 00:48:07,300
Oh, Mrs. Lincoln, you're right.

694
00:48:07,500 --> 00:48:10,600
My wealth should offer me no advantage.

695
00:48:10,800 --> 00:48:14,900
However, since my ancestors
founded Gatlin...

696
00:48:15,100 --> 00:48:18,000
...my holdings do give me a little leverage.

697
00:48:18,300 --> 00:48:21,800
For example, if I were to donate the old mill...

698
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:26,100
...to, say, a drug rehabilitation center?

699
00:48:26,200 --> 00:48:27,300
(ALL GASP)

700
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:28,800
Oh, my God.

701
00:48:28,900 --> 00:48:32,600
There again, I own the land
the Wayward Dog motel stands on.

702
00:48:32,800 --> 00:48:36,900
Its closure would cause a little inconvenience
to one or two of you gentlemen. Heh.

703
00:48:37,100 --> 00:48:40,000
You'd have to travel out of town
to see your lady friends...

704
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:44,700
...when your wives believe that you are
attending yet another meeting...

705
00:48:44,900 --> 00:48:47,600
...of the American Civil War
Reenactment Society.

706
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:53,700
So might I presume that this matter
is now comfortably...

707
00:48:53,900 --> 00:48:55,300
...laid to rest?

708
00:48:57,000 --> 00:48:59,200
I'm not afraid of you or your evil kind.

709
00:48:59,400 --> 00:49:03,200
God our creator will condemn you
to hellfire along with terrorists...

710
00:49:03,300 --> 00:49:08,400
...atheists, homosexuals,
Democrats, Liberals, Socialists...

711
00:49:08,500 --> 00:49:12,400
...Greenpeace
and all the other unnatural abominations.

712
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:15,200
My dear Mrs. Lincoln.

713
00:49:15,300 --> 00:49:19,000
If I were you,
I would welcome any kind of fire.

714
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:24,200
Might give you the opportunity
to burn that unfortunate hat you're wearing.

715
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:30,100
(SARAFINE LAUGHING)

716
00:49:38,300 --> 00:49:40,100
Sarafine.

717
00:49:43,700 --> 00:49:48,300
Well, I would have expected to find you
in something a little more chic.

718
00:49:48,500 --> 00:49:51,300
Oh, come on, Macon.

719
00:49:51,400 --> 00:49:55,500
She's perfect.
She's a pillar of the community.

720
00:49:55,700 --> 00:49:58,700
You're right about the hat, though.
Ain't it tragic?

721
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:01,800
But if you borrow the body,
you have to borrow the closet...

722
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:06,900
...and, my dear, you would think
the woman invented the housecoat.

723
00:50:07,100 --> 00:50:09,100
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

724
00:50:10,700 --> 00:50:13,200
So let's see now.

725
00:50:13,600 --> 00:50:15,200
Have you missed your little sister?

726
00:50:15,300 --> 00:50:16,900
No.

727
00:50:17,600 --> 00:50:19,100
Hmm.

728
00:50:19,200 --> 00:50:24,200
Don't be unkind.
You used to love playing in the Dark.

729
00:50:24,800 --> 00:50:26,400
Remember?

730
00:50:28,200 --> 00:50:31,200
I can feel your powers waning.

731
00:50:31,400 --> 00:50:37,300
Hmm, that's so sad. They're fading,
and you know why that is.

732
00:50:37,900 --> 00:50:43,100
That's what comes of pretending
to be something you're not.

733
00:50:44,600 --> 00:50:45,800
Oh.

734
00:50:45,900 --> 00:50:48,300
Daddy's tie-pin. That is so sweet.

735
00:50:49,300 --> 00:50:52,400
The curse is gonna claim her, Macon.

736
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:57,900
You're not quite sure, though, are you?

737
00:50:59,300 --> 00:51:00,600
SARAFINE: Hmm.

738
00:51:00,800 --> 00:51:04,100
If you were certain,
then why bring the boy into it?

739
00:51:04,200 --> 00:51:06,600
I didn't bring the boy into it.

740
00:51:06,800 --> 00:51:09,200
Love brought him in.

741
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:13,500
Lena and the mortal have been on their way
to each other since they were born.

742
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:17,000
They have that terrible thing, "destiny."
Even your Lila sensed that.

743
00:51:17,200 --> 00:51:21,500
And you know the law of the curse:
no Caster may love a mortal.

744
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:25,000
Mind you, it couldn't worked out better
if I had planned it.

745
00:51:25,200 --> 00:51:28,300
That first love, Oh.

746
00:51:28,500 --> 00:51:30,200
Such joy.

747
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:32,500
Such beauty.

748
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:35,600
And that first heartbreak.

749
00:51:36,500 --> 00:51:38,300
So bitter.

750
00:51:39,100 --> 00:51:40,900
So painful.

751
00:51:41,100 --> 00:51:43,600
That's enough to turn any girl Dark...

752
00:51:44,100 --> 00:51:46,200
...mortal or Caster.

753
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:47,400
(SARAFINE CHUCKLES)

754
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:49,000
I'm so excited.

755
00:51:49,100 --> 00:51:53,900
Lena's birthday is gonna fall on
the most powerful solstice in 5000 years.

756
00:51:54,000 --> 00:51:58,300
More energy is gonna be released than ever
before and this Earth's cycle will be over.

757
00:51:58,500 --> 00:52:02,700
She's gonna be more powerful than either
of us, Macon, and she will lead us all.

758
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:04,600
Toward what?

759
00:52:04,700 --> 00:52:07,400
An age without hiding.

760
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:11,200
I'm... I'm so...

761
00:52:12,900 --> 00:52:15,400
...tired of hiding!

762
00:52:16,100 --> 00:52:20,400
These parasites have had their own way
long enough, don't you think?

763
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:26,100
Oh, here's a good game.
Name one species that'll miss them.

764
00:52:26,200 --> 00:52:28,200
See? You can't.

765
00:52:28,300 --> 00:52:33,000
Because mortals do nothing
but consume and destroy.

766
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,800
They invent ideas...

767
00:52:36,100 --> 00:52:40,500
...like God, and love, and righteousness...

768
00:52:40,700 --> 00:52:44,500
...and then they use those same ideas
to kill anyone who disagrees with them.

769
00:52:44,600 --> 00:52:47,400
You really want to hang out
with those people?

770
00:52:47,600 --> 00:52:51,100
They pray without true beliefs
and then wonder why their spells don't work.

771
00:52:51,300 --> 00:52:53,700
They don't even value
their pathetic little lives...

772
00:52:53,900 --> 00:52:56,200
...until seconds before it's taken from them.

773
00:52:56,400 --> 00:52:57,800
Poor things.

774
00:52:58,300 --> 00:53:00,200
It's our turn, Macon.

775
00:53:00,400 --> 00:53:02,300
Darling, come back.

776
00:53:02,900 --> 00:53:04,400
Come back.

777
00:53:04,500 --> 00:53:07,300
- Lena will put an end to them.
- No.

778
00:53:07,900 --> 00:53:11,200
Lena will not turn Dark. She's too strong.

779
00:53:11,400 --> 00:53:15,500
She has got no choice in the matter,
my darling.

780
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:18,400
The curse has already begun.

781
00:53:18,800 --> 00:53:21,300
No. That is a lie!

782
00:53:24,900 --> 00:53:26,500
What's a lie, Mr. Ravenwood?

783
00:53:28,300 --> 00:53:29,800
My apologies.

784
00:53:31,100 --> 00:53:32,800
Lena will return to school.

785
00:53:33,500 --> 00:53:35,800
And that is an end of it.

786
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:37,900
(MURMURING)

787
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:46,800
Wow, you and Lena Duchannes.

788
00:53:47,000 --> 00:53:49,200
Ugh, yeah, don't tell anybody.

789
00:53:49,200 --> 00:53:53,200
Oh, come on, and miss the chance
to see Emily shit nails?

790
00:53:53,400 --> 00:53:55,300
I bet Lena could actually do that.

791
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:56,500
What?

792
00:53:56,700 --> 00:53:57,700
(CAR APPROACHING)

793
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:33,900
Which one of you lucky boys is Ethan Wate?

794
00:54:37,600 --> 00:54:38,600
Well?

795
00:54:39,100 --> 00:54:41,600
Which one of you has the power of tongue?

796
00:54:41,800 --> 00:54:44,900
Me am. I'm... Me Ethan.

797
00:54:45,500 --> 00:54:47,300
Ethan!

798
00:54:50,700 --> 00:54:52,600
- Do I know you?
- Not a bit.

799
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:56,200
- I'm Ridley Duchannes. Follow me.
ETHAN: - You're a relative of Lane's?

800
00:54:56,300 --> 00:54:59,100
Honey, you are looking at the relative.

801
00:54:59,300 --> 00:55:02,800
- Uh, oh, this is my friend Link.
- Sincere pleasure, Link.

802
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:05,600
Oh, I... Uh... Wha...

803
00:55:05,700 --> 00:55:08,000
- Get in.
ETHAN: - Oh, I wasn't invited.

804
00:55:08,100 --> 00:55:10,600
I don't think her uncle would, uh, like...

805
00:55:10,800 --> 00:55:14,600
Trust me, family's dying to meet you.

806
00:55:20,200 --> 00:55:21,300
(ENGINE REVS)

807
00:55:36,900 --> 00:55:38,200
Ravenwood.

808
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:40,300
Been a long time.

809
00:55:43,800 --> 00:55:46,500
Lena and I are more like sisters
than cousins.

810
00:55:46,700 --> 00:55:48,800
I'm surprised she hasn't mentioned me.

811
00:55:48,900 --> 00:55:53,400
But then, I'm sure I couldn't count high enough
all the things Lena hasn't mentioned.

812
00:55:53,600 --> 00:55:54,900
(RIDLEY SIGHS)

813
00:55:56,200 --> 00:55:58,800
Oh. Why, thank you, kind sir.

814
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:00,900
Do I look okay?

815
00:56:01,100 --> 00:56:04,100
Always get a little nervous seeing the family.

816
00:56:04,900 --> 00:56:06,700
You have lovely eyes.

817
00:56:07,300 --> 00:56:08,700
Mm.

818
00:56:09,100 --> 00:56:11,100
You're lucky those lips are spoken for.

819
00:56:11,300 --> 00:56:12,900
May I?

820
00:56:13,300 --> 00:56:15,400
Mm. Such a gentleman too.

821
00:56:19,900 --> 00:56:21,500
Night, mother.

822
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:23,400
Ridley. Oh.

823
00:56:23,500 --> 00:56:24,600
(DOOR CLOSES)

824
00:56:24,700 --> 00:56:26,300
I told you to stay away.

825
00:56:26,500 --> 00:56:29,900
Why, I couldn't miss a holiday
with my family now, could I, Mama?

826
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:32,200
MACON: Well, well.

827
00:56:32,400 --> 00:56:36,400
Ridley, my dear.
What an unpleasant surprise.

828
00:56:36,500 --> 00:56:39,800
Uncle Macon. How old and weak you look.

829
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:43,100
- I distinctly remember forgetting to invite you.
- Heh.

830
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:46,100
And I told you
never to cross this threshold again.

831
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:50,100
What?

832
00:56:50,800 --> 00:56:54,300
- What have you done to him?
- Invited him to dinner with the folks, is all.

833
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:56,600
Well...

834
00:56:57,000 --> 00:57:01,700
Why don't you escort your under-dressed
friend into the dining room?

835
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:06,400
I wasn't...

836
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:07,800
MACON: - Del.
- Wha...?

837
00:57:12,700 --> 00:57:14,300
RIDLEY: Hello, coz.

838
00:57:15,500 --> 00:57:18,000
- Don't you look pretty.
- Ethan?

839
00:57:18,200 --> 00:57:20,200
- Uh, ah-
- Oh.

840
00:57:20,400 --> 00:57:23,700
Isn't that sweet? He's all choked up.

841
00:57:23,700 --> 00:57:25,900
- Must be love.
- Oh.

842
00:57:26,100 --> 00:57:27,600
- Macon.
MACON: - It's all right, Lena.

843
00:57:27,700 --> 00:57:29,800
She can do no real harm here.

844
00:57:30,000 --> 00:57:32,900
- You sure about that, Macon?
- Don't you sass your uncle, now.

845
00:57:33,100 --> 00:57:36,400
Del, why don't you get two place settings
for our uninvited guests?

846
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:37,800
- Oh.
MACON: - Thank you.

847
00:57:38,000 --> 00:57:40,300
You sit near me, sugar.

848
00:57:40,400 --> 00:57:42,700
Sit right over here.

849
00:57:44,300 --> 00:57:46,100
LARKIN: - Sis?
RIDLEY: - Larkin.

850
00:57:46,300 --> 00:57:48,900
Ethan, this is my younger brother Larkin.

851
00:57:49,100 --> 00:57:51,500
LARKIN:
Didn't think I'd be seeing you here.

852
00:57:51,700 --> 00:57:54,600
- And who is the stiff?
RIDLEY: - Larkin, meet Ethan Wate.

853
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:56,000
LARKIN: Well, well.

854
00:57:56,200 --> 00:57:57,400
(RIDLEY GASPS)

855
00:57:57,600 --> 00:58:01,100
And this is our dear sweet Gramma...

856
00:58:01,300 --> 00:58:03,800
...who we all just love to death.

857
00:58:05,000 --> 00:58:07,600
We weren't expecting you, child.

858
00:58:07,800 --> 00:58:09,500
Let me have a look at you.

859
00:58:09,600 --> 00:58:10,600
(GRUNTS)

860
00:58:10,800 --> 00:58:12,500
Why is it, Ridley...

861
00:58:12,700 --> 00:58:17,100
...that when I look into your eyes,
all I can see are hers?

862
00:58:17,300 --> 00:58:19,900
You two are as thick as thieves, aren't you?

863
00:58:20,100 --> 00:58:21,500
Mother.

864
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:25,500
(RIDLEY GRUNTS)

865
00:58:27,600 --> 00:58:29,600
MACON: How about a little music...

866
00:58:29,700 --> 00:58:33,500
...and why don't we all just sit down
and enjoy ourselves?

867
00:58:33,600 --> 00:58:35,600
And let's have some wine.

868
00:58:37,100 --> 00:58:38,600
DEL: Something to drink?

869
00:58:48,200 --> 00:58:49,800
MACON: Here, allow me.

870
00:58:50,300 --> 00:58:52,500
Ah. Mama's homemade macaroons.

871
00:58:52,700 --> 00:58:54,200
DEL: Oh, heh.

872
00:58:54,300 --> 00:58:55,800
RIDLEY: I've missed these.

873
00:58:56,000 --> 00:59:00,600
So, coz, any big plans for your birthday?

874
00:59:00,800 --> 00:59:04,500
Nothing to concern yourself with.
You won't be invited, coz.

875
00:59:04,700 --> 00:59:08,300
Well, Lena, darling, you should.

876
00:59:09,100 --> 00:59:11,900
Be concerned, that is.
Such an important birthday.

877
00:59:12,100 --> 00:59:13,300
That's enough, Ridley.

878
00:59:13,400 --> 00:59:18,700
I had hoped that we'd have a holiday meal
we would all survive.

879
00:59:18,900 --> 00:59:20,400
What do you want?

880
00:59:20,600 --> 00:59:23,300
Just to be with my family again, coz.

881
00:59:23,500 --> 00:59:25,300
You've been claimed by the Dark.

882
00:59:26,000 --> 00:59:28,000
You're no longer part of this family.

883
00:59:28,200 --> 00:59:32,400
Ridley, sweetheart, there's nothing
we can do for you now. I'm so sorry.

884
00:59:32,600 --> 00:59:34,900
No hard feelings, Mama.

885
00:59:35,400 --> 00:59:37,100
But Lena and I are the same.

886
00:59:37,300 --> 00:59:40,300
I wonder, when she goes Dark...

887
00:59:41,400 --> 00:59:44,300
- ...will you shut her out too?
- That's enough.

888
00:59:44,400 --> 00:59:47,700
You think you can keep Lena so good,
so innocent?

889
00:59:48,500 --> 00:59:50,600
Wasn't I the same before I was Claimed?

890
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:53,900
As I recall, you were a spoiled brat
from the moment you were born.

891
00:59:54,100 --> 00:59:55,100
Maybe I was just unloved.

892
00:59:55,300 --> 00:59:56,800
Ugh. I did the best I could.

893
00:59:57,000 --> 00:59:59,500
And look at what I am now.

894
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:01,600
Oh, that's right, blame the mother.

895
01:00:01,800 --> 01:00:05,700
You think Lena is a good girl now,
but it won't matter.

896
01:00:05,800 --> 01:00:09,300
Even if her true nature doesn't claim her
for the Dark, the curse will.

897
01:00:09,500 --> 01:00:10,600
It's already started.

898
01:00:10,800 --> 01:00:12,200
- I'm warning you.
- What curse?

899
01:00:12,400 --> 01:00:15,400
- Pay no mind to her lies.
- You know it's true.

900
01:00:16,300 --> 01:00:17,700
Ah! Aw.

901
01:00:17,800 --> 01:00:19,700
Look at my manners.

902
01:00:19,800 --> 01:00:23,200
Here, honey. Let me serve you.

903
01:00:24,000 --> 01:00:26,000
Get away from him!

904
01:00:28,500 --> 01:00:30,300
Oh, really, coz?

905
01:00:40,200 --> 01:00:42,100
Lena, will you stop this?

906
01:00:44,600 --> 01:00:45,600
Stop it!

907
01:00:47,900 --> 01:00:48,900
(RIDLEY LAUGHS)

908
01:00:49,100 --> 01:00:52,000
RIDLEY:
Oh, just another good girl gone bad, I guess.

909
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:54,800
GRAMMA: Lena, child, there's no need for this.

910
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:56,500
Will you stop this immediately?

911
01:00:58,200 --> 01:01:01,200
Breaking windows on poor,
helpless little mortals.

912
01:01:01,300 --> 01:01:03,900
She's already closer to the Dark than I was!

913
01:01:04,100 --> 01:01:06,800
- You know that's a lie!
- I want you out of here.

914
01:01:06,900 --> 01:01:08,300
(RIDLEY LAUGHS)

915
01:01:09,300 --> 01:01:11,600
GRAMMA:
Ridley, don't make me get up from this table!

916
01:01:11,700 --> 01:01:13,500
(DISHES RATTLING AND BREAKING)

917
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:22,400
I am so sick of everyone treating you
like you're something special!

918
01:01:22,500 --> 01:01:24,800
There's nothing special about you!

919
01:01:24,900 --> 01:01:29,300
Go on, you tell her, Macon!
You know how she will be Claimed!

920
01:01:29,400 --> 01:01:32,200
I said, get away from my boyfriend,
you witch.

921
01:01:32,400 --> 01:01:33,500
(SCREAMS)

922
01:01:41,300 --> 01:01:42,500
GRAMMA: Oh.

923
01:01:44,200 --> 01:01:46,100
LARKIN: Oh, Lord.

924
01:01:56,200 --> 01:01:58,200
Boyfriend, huh? Heh.

925
01:02:00,500 --> 01:02:02,500
Is he gonna be all right?

926
01:02:03,100 --> 01:02:04,900
GRAMMA: He'll be fine.

927
01:02:06,400 --> 01:02:08,300
What curse was Ridley talking about?

928
01:02:08,500 --> 01:02:13,100
Ridley was just telling stories
to get your rage going, to lose control.

929
01:02:13,300 --> 01:02:15,100
You mustn't let her.

930
01:02:17,200 --> 01:02:20,100
Larkin, help me take him to my room.

931
01:02:20,200 --> 01:02:23,800
Oh. He will. Heh.

932
01:02:26,200 --> 01:02:30,500
Sitting there eating through a Caster combat
like you're two sandwiches shy of a picnic.

933
01:02:30,600 --> 01:02:33,900
LARKIN: Better be a sandwich
when I get back. I'm still hungry.

934
01:02:34,100 --> 01:02:36,900
Did you see the way she looks at the boy?

935
01:02:37,000 --> 01:02:39,600
There's no getting in-between them now.

936
01:02:40,100 --> 01:02:42,300
Then it has begun.

937
01:02:57,700 --> 01:02:59,300
ETHAN: Hey, there.

938
01:03:01,700 --> 01:03:03,600
How do you feel?

939
01:03:04,900 --> 01:03:09,000
Like I was in a tornado inside a dining room.
No big deal.

940
01:03:09,800 --> 01:03:13,400
I'm so sorry about Ridley.
I didn't know she was back.

941
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:17,100
Yeah. She's sort of a bitch, isn't she?

942
01:03:17,200 --> 01:03:19,300
She's a siren.

943
01:03:19,800 --> 01:03:24,500
She can make mortals see,
think or do whatever she wants...

944
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:26,600
...especially men.

945
01:03:27,500 --> 01:03:29,800
Isn't that, like, the working definition
of a bitch?

946
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:31,400
(LENA CHUCKLES)

947
01:03:32,000 --> 01:03:34,300
She wasn't always like that.

948
01:03:36,000 --> 01:03:39,200
We were like sisters. You know?

949
01:03:39,400 --> 01:03:43,700
Traveled together so much
we shared the same suitcase.

950
01:03:44,500 --> 01:03:49,300
Did homework, watched Disney.
We were just kids.

951
01:03:51,600 --> 01:03:55,000
<i>The night Ridley turned 16, she ran away.</i>

952
01:03:55,200 --> 01:03:58,300
<i>She said she could feel herself turning Dark.</i>

953
01:03:59,200 --> 01:04:03,200
<i>She said she had to get away
before she hurt anybody she loved.</i>

954
01:04:03,400 --> 01:04:05,600
<i>Before she hurt me.</i>

955
01:04:06,100 --> 01:04:07,900
<i>I followed her.</i>

956
01:04:09,200 --> 01:04:11,000
<i>Then it happened.</i>

957
01:04:11,200 --> 01:04:13,200
(GASPS)

958
01:04:38,700 --> 01:04:40,700
(MEN CHATTERING AND
LAUGHING NEARBY)

959
01:04:49,500 --> 01:04:52,600
MAN 1: - That was better.
MAN 2: - That's what I'm talking about!

960
01:04:53,800 --> 01:04:55,600
MAN 3: Guys, hold up a second.

961
01:04:55,800 --> 01:04:57,500
No, I gotta go. I gotta go. Hold on.

962
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:13,100
LENA: <i>I saw it all.</i>

963
01:05:48,400 --> 01:05:50,400
She loved me.

964
01:05:50,600 --> 01:05:51,700
I know it.

965
01:05:51,900 --> 01:05:53,700
It's not fair what happened to her.

966
01:05:54,400 --> 01:05:56,300
And the same thing could happen to me.

967
01:05:56,500 --> 01:05:57,700
It won't.

968
01:05:57,900 --> 01:06:00,300
Did you see me tonight?

969
01:06:00,500 --> 01:06:01,800
I can't control myself.

970
01:06:01,900 --> 01:06:07,000
Lena, I don't believe that we have
one fate and no choice.

971
01:06:07,400 --> 01:06:09,800
We make our own lives.

972
01:06:13,200 --> 01:06:15,900
ETHAN;
Two, please. Thank you. This is Lena. Lena.

973
01:06:16,000 --> 01:06:17,500
MAN: - Hi, Lena.
LENA: - Hi.

974
01:06:17,600 --> 01:06:20,900
- Here, I gotta give you the money, heh.
- Heh.

975
01:06:21,100 --> 01:06:23,300
MAN: - Let me get your change.
- Thanks.

976
01:06:23,800 --> 01:06:25,700
MAN: There you go.

977
01:06:26,400 --> 01:06:28,600
ETHAN: - You good? Your kids are good?
MAN: - Oh, yeah.

978
01:06:28,600 --> 01:06:30,100
ETHAN: Good.

979
01:06:32,200 --> 01:06:33,800
GIRL: You got the tickets?

980
01:06:35,300 --> 01:06:36,500
Hi.

981
01:06:36,600 --> 01:06:37,700
BOY: Get a load of this.

982
01:06:37,800 --> 01:06:39,400
(EMILY CHUCKLES)

983
01:06:41,400 --> 01:06:44,800
You know, maybe you have Ethan fooled,
but not me.

984
01:06:45,000 --> 01:06:46,400
Oh, shucks.

985
01:06:46,500 --> 01:06:49,800
Ahem. Uh, chill, girl. Chill, chill.

986
01:06:52,900 --> 01:06:54,900
(ORCHESTRAL MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)

987
01:06:57,700 --> 01:06:59,400
EMILY: - See the look on her face?
- Ha, ha.

988
01:06:59,600 --> 01:07:01,300
EMILY: I see right through her.

989
01:07:01,500 --> 01:07:04,200
Hi. Just, uh... Just one, please.

990
01:07:04,300 --> 01:07:06,000
MAN: Alrighty.

991
01:07:08,200 --> 01:07:09,700
There you go.

992
01:07:44,100 --> 01:07:47,200
Do not let them bother you, okay?

993
01:07:48,000 --> 01:07:50,200
(FILM CHARACTERS
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

994
01:07:54,900 --> 01:07:57,900
MAN: (ON SCREEN) <i>Yeah, I've been up
since 5. Feeling pretty good, though.</i>

995
01:07:58,600 --> 01:08:00,700
Heh. You want Milk Duds?

996
01:08:00,800 --> 01:08:02,700
LENA:
What do you put them in your pocket for?

997
01:08:02,800 --> 01:08:06,600
I have to hide some for myself,
because Link never shares.

998
01:08:07,000 --> 01:08:09,600
MAN: (ON SCREEN)
All right. I mean, I've been doing better...

999
01:08:11,000 --> 01:08:15,600
Oh. I'm so sorry. I didn't realize I had that.

1000
01:08:17,500 --> 01:08:19,400
No, it's okay.

1001
01:08:19,600 --> 01:08:21,100
I wanna see.

1002
01:08:21,300 --> 01:08:23,100
WOMAN: (ON SCREEN) <i>Be right there.</i>

1003
01:08:37,900 --> 01:08:39,800
MAN: <i>
Yeah, whatever you can find!</i>

1004
01:08:41,000 --> 01:08:43,500
<i>There's gold in there, and silver, get it all!</i>

1005
01:08:57,000 --> 01:08:58,200
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

1006
01:08:58,300 --> 01:09:00,900
GENEVIEVE: <i>- Oh, my God!</i>
ETHAN CARTER: <i>- Genevieve!</i>

1007
01:09:02,000 --> 01:09:03,100
GENEVIEVE: Ethan!

1008
01:09:03,300 --> 01:09:04,500
(ETHAN CARTER YELLS)

1009
01:09:05,000 --> 01:09:06,500
GENEVIEVE: Ethan.

1010
01:09:08,200 --> 01:09:10,600
Don't you dare. Okay, don't you dare
go anywhere.

1011
01:09:10,800 --> 01:09:13,500
Don't you dare, Ethan Carter Wate!

1012
01:09:14,800 --> 01:09:17,700
(SOBBING)
Come back. Wait, Ethan.

1013
01:09:28,500 --> 01:09:31,200
Body of my body, marrow and mind...

1014
01:09:31,300 --> 01:09:34,100
<i>...soul of my soul, to our spirit bind...</i>

1015
01:09:34,200 --> 01:09:36,500
<i>blood of my heart, my tide, my moon...</i>

1016
01:09:36,600 --> 01:09:40,400
...blood of my heart, my salvation, my doom!

1017
01:09:44,600 --> 01:09:46,300
Genevieve.

1018
01:09:47,300 --> 01:09:49,400
Was I shot?

1019
01:09:49,500 --> 01:09:51,100
What happened to your eyes?

1020
01:09:55,000 --> 01:09:56,800
(GRUNTING)

1021
01:10:22,400 --> 01:10:23,600
Form up, company!

1022
01:10:23,700 --> 01:10:25,100
At the ready!

1023
01:10:25,200 --> 01:10:26,300
Fire!

1024
01:10:30,500 --> 01:10:35,200
SARAFINE: <i>Oh, my darling Lena,
do you see now how you must be Claimed?</i>

1025
01:10:35,300 --> 01:10:38,100
<i>We are the descendants of Genevieve.</i>

1026
01:10:38,300 --> 01:10:41,400
<i>Her Dark power is in our blood.</i>

1027
01:10:41,600 --> 01:10:44,400
<i>Oh, how I've missed you, my daughter.</i>

1028
01:10:45,100 --> 01:10:48,300
<i>Your mother, Sarafine,
has come home for you.</i>

1029
01:10:48,500 --> 01:10:50,600
(LENA SHRIEKS)
(AUDIENCE MURMURING)

1030
01:10:50,800 --> 01:10:53,200
Guess Satan hates sequels too.

1031
01:10:53,300 --> 01:10:54,900
(AUDIENCE CHUCKLING)

1032
01:11:05,200 --> 01:11:06,800
AMMA: It's over.

1033
01:11:13,100 --> 01:11:14,300
There is no more.

1034
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:17,100
It's served its purpose.

1035
01:11:19,000 --> 01:11:20,000
(DOOR OPENS)

1036
01:11:20,200 --> 01:11:21,300
MACON: Lena?

1037
01:11:21,500 --> 01:11:24,100
The curse began
with your great-great-great grandmother.

1038
01:11:24,200 --> 01:11:26,700
Genevieve Katherine Duchannes.

1039
01:11:26,800 --> 01:11:30,200
She had the temerity
to fall in love with a mortal...

1040
01:11:30,600 --> 01:11:33,100
...your ancestor, Ethan Carter Wate.

1041
01:11:33,300 --> 01:11:37,500
In 1864, he deserted.
Came home to his Genevieve.

1042
01:11:37,800 --> 01:11:40,800
But he was killed in front of her eyes,
by Union soldiers...

1043
01:11:40,900 --> 01:11:44,300
...who were ransacking Greenbrier
during the battle of Honey Hill.

1044
01:11:44,800 --> 01:11:51,100
And in her madness, in her grief,
she used a spell that is forbidden to us.

1045
01:11:51,200 --> 01:11:52,800
To bring him back to life.

1046
01:11:54,000 --> 01:11:56,100
A spell that left a curse?

1047
01:11:56,200 --> 01:11:58,200
No Caster may reverse death.

1048
01:11:58,400 --> 01:12:02,200
So she lost her soul,
consumed by darkness forever.

1049
01:12:02,400 --> 01:12:05,500
But the spell worked.
If Genevieve loved him, why'd she kill him?

1050
01:12:05,700 --> 01:12:09,600
In that kind of darkness,
there's not even a memory of love, only power.

1051
01:12:09,800 --> 01:12:12,800
Everything has a price.

1052
01:12:28,600 --> 01:12:31,200
LENA: You told me my mother was dead.

1053
01:12:31,300 --> 01:12:34,100
You lied to me. Why? Why?

1054
01:12:34,200 --> 01:12:36,200
Lena! Our words, our language...

1055
01:12:36,300 --> 01:12:40,000
...cannot explain all that there is.
There are other ways someone can die to us.

1056
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:41,300
MACON: No, I'll tell her.

1057
01:12:41,500 --> 01:12:47,000
Your mother, Sarafine,
is the most powerful Dark Caster of all of us.

1058
01:12:47,800 --> 01:12:50,500
She lives in the darkness, in the shadows.

1059
01:12:50,700 --> 01:12:54,100
If she does appear,
it's in the guise of someone else.

1060
01:12:54,200 --> 01:12:56,600
She has no love for you.

1061
01:12:56,800 --> 01:12:58,900
That's what I was trying to protect you from.

1062
01:12:59,100 --> 01:13:01,400
I'm gonna be claimed for the Dark,
no matter what?

1063
01:13:01,600 --> 01:13:03,600
No, not necessarily.

1064
01:13:03,700 --> 01:13:06,400
I know your true nature, it's strong.

1065
01:13:06,600 --> 01:13:10,100
Sarafine recognizes it too.
She knows that without the curse...

1066
01:13:10,200 --> 01:13:13,500
...your true nature
would claim you for the Light.

1067
01:13:13,600 --> 01:13:16,100
No, I believe the curse can be broken.

1068
01:13:16,600 --> 01:13:21,400
But you need to have a will that's so strong
you control your own nature.

1069
01:13:21,600 --> 01:13:24,300
- That's what I told her.
- First thing you do, get rid of him.

1070
01:13:24,400 --> 01:13:26,300
- Wait, what?
- Sarafine's using you.

1071
01:13:26,500 --> 01:13:28,300
- That's not true.
MACON: - Listen to me, Lena.

1072
01:13:28,400 --> 01:13:30,400
- No, listen to me...
- Ethan, Manson's right.

1073
01:13:30,600 --> 01:13:34,000
If you're to break this curse,
you have to control your emotions.

1074
01:13:34,200 --> 01:13:36,900
And loving this boy
puts you in terrible danger!

1075
01:13:37,000 --> 01:13:39,600
How could you know?
You never loved anyone.

1076
01:13:39,700 --> 01:13:41,700
You despise mortals.

1077
01:13:41,800 --> 01:13:46,300
You never even had a friend,
even in our world. How could you know?

1078
01:13:49,700 --> 01:13:53,900
I know that no good
can come from us loving a mortal.

1079
01:13:56,100 --> 01:13:59,800
Lena, listen to me. There's gotta be a way,
another way to break the curse.

1080
01:14:00,000 --> 01:14:01,600
AMMA: Macon!

1081
01:14:01,800 --> 01:14:04,100
- Don't even think that, young man!
- No!

1082
01:14:04,800 --> 01:14:08,700
You'll get the both of you killed.
You have to get out of her life.

1083
01:14:08,900 --> 01:14:10,900
Do you hear me?

1084
01:14:13,900 --> 01:14:17,800
Lena, say your goodbyes.

1085
01:14:25,500 --> 01:14:27,800
ETHAN: <i>Mason's keeping Lena at Ravenwood.</i>

1086
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:29,600
<i>He won't let me see her.</i>

1087
01:14:29,800 --> 01:14:33,000
<i>He thinks keeping us apart
is the best thing for her.</i>

1088
01:14:33,100 --> 01:14:35,500
<i>But he's wrong. I know Lena.</i>

1089
01:14:36,400 --> 01:14:38,500
<i>I know her like I know myself.</i>

1090
01:14:38,700 --> 01:14:43,600
<i>And I can feel her slipping away
into some place where I can't reach her.</i>

1091
01:14:54,000 --> 01:14:55,200
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

1092
01:14:57,200 --> 01:15:02,500
WOMAN: (ON TV)
<i>Go away, go away, go away, go away!</i>

1093
01:15:10,600 --> 01:15:11,700
- Hi, clear.
ETHAN: - Oh.

1094
01:15:11,900 --> 01:15:15,200
- Hello, Mrs. Lincoln. Just a minute.
MRS. LINCOLN: - Hi, dear.

1095
01:15:18,000 --> 01:15:19,700
Oh, dear.

1096
01:15:20,200 --> 01:15:21,800
This door seems to be stuck.

1097
01:15:21,900 --> 01:15:24,300
It's just these old houses.
They're such a nuisance.

1098
01:15:24,500 --> 01:15:26,000
- Yes, ma'am.
- They warp.

1099
01:15:26,200 --> 01:15:28,700
- Link's not here.
- Oh, I know, I know.

1100
01:15:28,800 --> 01:15:31,900
He's at Savannah Snow's party,
which is where all the kids are.

1101
01:15:32,100 --> 01:15:34,800
I had to make quite a number
of phone calls...

1102
01:15:35,000 --> 01:15:37,600
...to get him an invitation
on account of his...

1103
01:15:37,800 --> 01:15:40,800
Well, on account of his friendship with you.

1104
01:15:41,000 --> 01:15:44,000
Oh, I'm sorry you had to go
to that trouble, ma'am.

1105
01:15:44,200 --> 01:15:46,300
Well, you should be at that party, Ethan...

1106
01:15:46,500 --> 01:15:51,200
...kicking up your heels with your real friends,
with the children who belong in this town.

1107
01:15:51,400 --> 01:15:53,400
I'm not much up for a party tonight, ma'am.

1108
01:15:53,600 --> 01:15:55,200
Oh, well, that's a shame.

1109
01:15:55,400 --> 01:15:58,000
Well, see, I... I made you some brownies.

1110
01:15:58,200 --> 01:16:02,700
I thought maybe I could come in
and we could talk.

1111
01:16:02,800 --> 01:16:04,500
My fight’s not with you, son.

1112
01:16:04,700 --> 01:16:07,000
It's not. Never has been.

1113
01:16:07,200 --> 01:16:09,900
It's just that girl
with her seductive quirkiness...

1114
01:16:10,000 --> 01:16:12,200
...and you being motherless and all.

1115
01:16:12,400 --> 01:16:14,600
May I come in?

1116
01:16:17,800 --> 01:16:20,200
No, ma'am. I... I don't think so.

1117
01:16:21,600 --> 01:16:25,000
Did I hear you correctly just then, Ethan?

1118
01:16:25,200 --> 01:16:29,600
Do I have to ask you again? May I come in?

1119
01:16:30,000 --> 01:16:32,200
No, ma'am, you may not.

1120
01:16:32,400 --> 01:16:34,900
But I have made you brownies.

1121
01:16:35,100 --> 01:16:38,700
I've made you brownies from scratch.

1122
01:16:43,200 --> 01:16:47,000
Well, slap my ass and call me Sally!

1123
01:16:47,200 --> 01:16:48,800
(LAUGHS)

1124
01:16:49,000 --> 01:16:53,400
Lena bound your house. Oh, that's so sweet.

1125
01:16:55,400 --> 01:16:57,800
As if.

1126
01:16:57,900 --> 01:16:59,200
SARAFINE: <i>I'm on your side, son.</i>

1127
01:16:59,400 --> 01:17:02,500
<i>What's a little curse
when it comes to true love?</i>

1128
01:17:02,600 --> 01:17:06,300
<i>Anyone can see you and Lena
are just meant for each other...</i>

1129
01:17:06,500 --> 01:17:08,600
<i>...till death do you part.</i>

1130
01:17:08,700 --> 01:17:10,500
(SARAFINE LAUGHS)

1131
01:17:59,400 --> 01:18:00,900
Lena?

1132
01:18:06,700 --> 01:18:09,000
MACON: Get out of this house.

1133
01:18:10,400 --> 01:18:11,700
Lena.

1134
01:18:13,600 --> 01:18:15,300
MACON: Keep her bound.

1135
01:18:16,700 --> 01:18:18,200
ETHAN: Lena.

1136
01:18:19,700 --> 01:18:23,000
Lena, can we please just go outside
for one second and talk? I need...

1137
01:18:23,200 --> 01:18:24,700
MACON: - Get out!
- No!

1138
01:18:24,900 --> 01:18:26,900
Please, son, for your own good.

1139
01:18:28,700 --> 01:18:30,800
You should really listen to them.

1140
01:18:30,900 --> 01:18:32,400
No!

1141
01:18:33,700 --> 01:18:36,400
I'm sick of listening to your family.

1142
01:18:36,600 --> 01:18:40,400
I have been chased, spun, hypnotized...

1143
01:18:40,600 --> 01:18:43,400
...paralyzed, and damn near killed
by your family.

1144
01:18:43,500 --> 01:18:46,000
I've been going out of my mind
for the last two weeks.

1145
01:18:46,100 --> 01:18:49,800
Now your mother shows up on my doorstep
and damn near gives me a heart attack!

1146
01:18:50,000 --> 01:18:53,300
But you know what?
I don't care about them, about the curse.

1147
01:18:53,400 --> 01:18:56,100
You are not going Dark
and you are not losing me.

1148
01:18:56,300 --> 01:18:59,900
No matter what you do,
no matter what they do to me, I'm still here.

1149
01:19:00,100 --> 01:19:02,000
Now what does that tell you?

1150
01:19:04,700 --> 01:19:08,400
MACON: How could the boy break our spell?
He has no power.

1151
01:19:09,600 --> 01:19:14,000
It's not we who protect her now, it's the boy.

1152
01:19:21,400 --> 01:19:22,700
Amma, we need your help.

1153
01:19:25,200 --> 01:19:26,500
Why come to me?

1154
01:19:26,700 --> 01:19:30,700
LENA: The way you talked about the locket,
about the curse.

1155
01:19:30,900 --> 01:19:34,700
Excuse me, Miss Amma,
but I think you know more than you're saying.

1156
01:19:36,600 --> 01:19:39,000
Please, Amma.

1157
01:19:42,200 --> 01:19:45,200
This isn't the place you're gonna find
anything you need.

1158
01:19:45,300 --> 01:19:47,000
Meet me in the back.

1159
01:20:18,300 --> 01:20:20,300
ETHAN:
This must run under the whole town.

1160
01:20:20,400 --> 01:20:25,200
The whole country.
Gatlin is like the capital of Caster America.

1161
01:20:25,400 --> 01:20:29,300
It used to be under Washington, D.C.
until Nancy Reagan made them move.

1162
01:20:29,500 --> 01:20:31,900
She was the only mortal
they were ever scared of.

1163
01:20:48,400 --> 01:20:50,400
They know a Caster's here.

1164
01:20:52,500 --> 01:20:54,900
Amma, why didn't you tell us about this?

1165
01:20:55,000 --> 01:20:57,400
A Keeper has to be asked.

1166
01:20:57,900 --> 01:21:00,500
A Keeper, as in you're a...?

1167
01:21:00,700 --> 01:21:06,200
The Caster Library has been the responsibility
of Seers like me for generations.

1168
01:21:08,500 --> 01:21:12,200
Something I had no choice about either,
by the way.

1169
01:21:12,900 --> 01:21:17,600
And these books hold the histories
of the Casters from around the world...

1170
01:21:17,700 --> 01:21:20,700
...the laws that keep balance
between Light and Dark.

1171
01:21:20,800 --> 01:21:23,100
Hey! Get away from that.

1172
01:21:24,100 --> 01:21:28,500
Macon comes here every day and reads
every book he can for the Forbidden Spell.

1173
01:21:29,000 --> 01:21:31,100
- He found nothing?
AMMA: - Mm-mm.

1174
01:21:32,800 --> 01:21:34,600
But you can do it.

1175
01:21:35,700 --> 01:21:39,900
God gives us what we can handle,
even if we don't believe it ourselves.

1176
01:21:42,600 --> 01:21:44,200
Close your eyes.

1177
01:21:45,800 --> 01:21:50,500
See with your mind what you're looking for
as if you've already found it.

1178
01:22:02,000 --> 01:22:03,400
I knew it.

1179
01:22:07,400 --> 01:22:08,700
<i>Book of Moons.</i>

1180
01:22:08,800 --> 01:22:10,900
It's the most powerful book
of the Otherworld.

1181
01:22:11,100 --> 01:22:14,800
It's as alive as you or me.
Strongest of every spells, good and bad.

1182
01:22:14,900 --> 01:22:17,200
- Did Macon look through it?
- No, he couldn't.

1183
01:22:17,300 --> 01:22:20,700
The Book chooses who reads it.
Its Law is "Like attracts Like."

1184
01:22:26,000 --> 01:22:28,500
There... There's no writing.

1185
01:22:28,700 --> 01:22:30,500
It won't reveal itself so easy.

1186
01:22:30,700 --> 01:22:36,200
A curse this dark takes its time showing itself.
The Dark will test you.

1187
01:22:36,700 --> 01:22:38,000
Don't worry, you'll find it.

1188
01:22:38,200 --> 01:22:40,900
Just look under
"How Not to Turn Into Your Mother."

1189
01:22:42,500 --> 01:22:44,000
(LENA CHUCKLES)

1190
01:22:47,000 --> 01:22:50,000
Come on. Come on.

1191
01:23:16,900 --> 01:23:20,800
ETHAN: <i>I've been taking Lena
to the Caster Library for weeks now.</i>

1192
01:23:24,700 --> 01:23:27,200
<i>But Lena's getting discouraged.</i>

1193
01:23:27,400 --> 01:23:31,100
<i>The longer this thing takes,
the more I see a change in her.</i>

1194
01:23:52,800 --> 01:23:54,400
We'll find a way, okay?

1195
01:23:54,600 --> 01:23:56,900
You're just a mortal, how would you know?

1196
01:23:57,100 --> 01:23:59,400
Hey, I can make wind.
Maybe not a hurricane...

1197
01:23:59,600 --> 01:24:03,300
- Why don't we just admit it?
- Admit what?

1198
01:24:03,400 --> 01:24:06,900
It's already started.
I'm turning into a Dark bitch, I can feel it.

1199
01:24:07,000 --> 01:24:10,500
No, Lena, you're just stressed. It's not...

1200
01:24:10,700 --> 01:24:13,700
It doesn't matter what causes it.

1201
01:24:13,800 --> 01:24:16,800
I'm turning
and you're just too stupid to see it.

1202
01:24:18,000 --> 01:24:19,900
Okay, now you're a bitch.

1203
01:24:20,900 --> 01:24:22,600
(THUNDER CRASHES)

1204
01:24:29,500 --> 01:24:31,800
Really? Is this necessary?

1205
01:24:32,900 --> 01:24:34,900
I'm agreeing with you.

1206
01:24:35,000 --> 01:24:38,200
Okay, I'm just a dumb-ass mortal
who can't make his own thunder.

1207
01:24:38,300 --> 01:24:40,500
But I know there's no way
we're gonna figure this out...

1208
01:24:40,700 --> 01:24:43,100
...unless you stop feeling so sorry
for yourself all the time!

1209
01:24:43,300 --> 01:24:44,600
(SCREAMS)

1210
01:24:44,800 --> 01:24:48,200
Go ahead! Start an earthquake,
see where it gets you.

1211
01:24:48,400 --> 01:24:51,000
Everybody has to deal with shit
in their lives, Lena.

1212
01:24:51,200 --> 01:24:52,700
What are you yelling at me for?

1213
01:24:53,600 --> 01:24:57,200
You want to be a normal human?
What do you think that is?

1214
01:24:57,400 --> 01:25:00,500
We don't have powers
to just change things whenever we like.

1215
01:25:00,700 --> 01:25:04,600
Being human is feeling bad,
it's feeling pissed off.

1216
01:25:04,700 --> 01:25:07,700
It's feeling scared
and not being able to do anything about it...

1217
01:25:07,900 --> 01:25:11,700
...until you don't feel that way anymore,
until you can see your way out of it.

1218
01:25:11,900 --> 01:25:14,000
And I yelled at you because I care about you!

1219
01:25:14,100 --> 01:25:17,000
That's what normal people do,
who love each other...

1220
01:25:17,200 --> 01:25:19,900
...when one of them is acting like a brat.

1221
01:25:20,100 --> 01:25:22,400
Now, would you please stop raining on me?

1222
01:25:52,900 --> 01:25:54,700
I'm sorry.

1223
01:25:57,500 --> 01:26:00,200
You've got to get away from me.

1224
01:26:02,300 --> 01:26:05,500
I don't know what I do, it just happens.

1225
01:26:05,700 --> 01:26:08,200
You still don't get it, do you?

1226
01:26:08,700 --> 01:26:12,000
I don't want to be any further away
from you than I am right now...

1227
01:26:12,100 --> 01:26:14,200
...one way or another.

1228
01:26:15,600 --> 01:26:18,600
I'm scared I'm gonna hurt you.

1229
01:26:19,000 --> 01:26:21,800
Well, love's a risk for anybody.

1230
01:26:22,200 --> 01:26:24,800
I mean, "kill you" hurt you.

1231
01:26:25,000 --> 01:26:26,600
Go ahead.

1232
01:26:27,200 --> 01:26:29,000
Kill me.

1233
01:27:04,900 --> 01:27:06,600
Oh! Ooh, ah.

1234
01:27:06,700 --> 01:27:11,000
What part of "You cannot touch it
if you are not a Caster" don't you understand?

1235
01:27:14,500 --> 01:27:16,700
There were Casters in the Civil War?

1236
01:27:16,900 --> 01:27:20,800
Casters have been fighting alongside mortals
for centuries, every war, every side.

1237
01:27:20,900 --> 01:27:23,900
Just because they're supernatural
don't make them any smarter.

1238
01:27:24,000 --> 01:27:26,000
You know, What I can't figure...

1239
01:27:26,200 --> 01:27:29,300
- ...is you go to church every Sunday.
- Mm-hm.

1240
01:27:29,400 --> 01:27:32,000
How do you believe in all this
and still believe in God?

1241
01:27:32,100 --> 01:27:33,800
God created all things, didn't he?

1242
01:27:34,000 --> 01:27:37,100
It's only men who go and decide
which ones are mistakes.

1243
01:27:44,400 --> 01:27:46,800
My mom came here, didn't she?

1244
01:27:51,500 --> 01:27:53,200
With Macon?

1245
01:27:56,800 --> 01:27:59,300
They met here many times.

1246
01:27:59,500 --> 01:28:02,100
Macon loved teaching her about his world.

1247
01:28:10,000 --> 01:28:12,300
Macon loved her, didn't he?

1248
01:28:12,600 --> 01:28:15,300
No one knows what Macon
can and can't feel, but...

1249
01:28:15,400 --> 01:28:17,100
...Lila sure got close.

1250
01:28:18,700 --> 01:28:20,300
Ethan?

1251
01:28:21,600 --> 01:28:23,400
She loved your father.

1252
01:28:32,500 --> 01:28:34,500
(HARMONICA PLAYS)

1253
01:28:38,700 --> 01:28:40,600
You going somewhere?

1254
01:28:40,800 --> 01:28:45,200
Wherever Lena is. Even if that's in Gatlin.

1255
01:28:46,300 --> 01:28:48,800
- What are you doing here?
- I don't know what...

1256
01:28:48,900 --> 01:28:52,300
...power you have over Lena, but, uh...

1257
01:28:53,200 --> 01:28:55,500
...I've come to ask you to...

1258
01:28:55,800 --> 01:28:56,900
...let her go.

1259
01:28:57,000 --> 01:28:59,300
I don't have any power, Macon.

1260
01:28:59,500 --> 01:29:00,800
I just love her.

1261
01:29:00,900 --> 01:29:03,500
Then just put an end to it.

1262
01:29:05,000 --> 01:29:06,100
I can't, heh.

1263
01:29:06,200 --> 01:29:11,100
Even if it means
destroying the Lena you love, hmm?

1264
01:29:11,200 --> 01:29:14,800
It can't, because there's no way
that what Lena and I feel for each other...

1265
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:18,500
...is gonna turn into something
wrong or evil.

1266
01:29:18,700 --> 01:29:20,000
There's no way.

1267
01:29:20,600 --> 01:29:23,400
As long as I live,
I'll never understand you creatures.

1268
01:29:23,900 --> 01:29:26,500
You have no real power.

1269
01:29:27,000 --> 01:29:30,200
You live at the mercy
of forces outside your control.

1270
01:29:31,300 --> 01:29:35,300
And yet, you believe that what you feel...

1271
01:29:35,500 --> 01:29:38,100
...will somehow make it all right.

1272
01:29:38,300 --> 01:29:40,900
Gotta have some faith, Macon.

1273
01:30:49,000 --> 01:30:50,400
Lena?

1274
01:30:50,700 --> 01:30:52,300
You okay?

1275
01:30:56,500 --> 01:30:57,800
Lena?

1276
01:31:04,500 --> 01:31:05,600
- Lena?
- Yeah?

1277
01:31:05,800 --> 01:31:08,200
- Is something wrong?
- No.

1278
01:31:08,300 --> 01:31:11,400
- I think I found something.
- Yeah?

1279
01:31:11,500 --> 01:31:13,400
What? Let me see.

1280
01:31:13,500 --> 01:31:16,500
Well, it's a lot to read, and...

1281
01:31:16,600 --> 01:31:20,600
...a lotto take in,
and I really got to concentrate.

1282
01:31:21,200 --> 01:31:22,500
ETHAN: Okay.

1283
01:31:23,400 --> 01:31:25,700
So I was wondering...

1284
01:31:28,100 --> 01:31:30,900
Well, I've gotta do it on my own, kind of.

1285
01:31:31,000 --> 01:31:34,200
You know, and if you're here,
you're just gonna distract me.

1286
01:31:34,400 --> 01:31:37,700
And I was wondering
if you wouldn't mind going home now.

1287
01:31:37,900 --> 01:31:41,600
And then, when I'm done, I'll call you later.

1288
01:31:44,700 --> 01:31:46,200
Is that okay?

1289
01:31:47,200 --> 01:31:48,700
Sure.

1290
01:31:49,800 --> 01:31:51,800
Whatever you want, okay?

1291
01:31:52,900 --> 01:31:54,400
Thanks.

1292
01:31:55,500 --> 01:31:57,200
I love you.

1293
01:31:59,800 --> 01:32:02,000
Okay, I'll talk to you later.

1294
01:32:18,900 --> 01:32:21,200
AMMA: Lena? He's gone.

1295
01:32:21,400 --> 01:32:23,600
(SOBBING)

1296
01:32:32,200 --> 01:32:33,400
It's okay.

1297
01:32:36,300 --> 01:32:37,700
Come on.

1298
01:32:38,000 --> 01:32:39,300
Come on.

1299
01:32:42,900 --> 01:32:44,500
Sit down. What is it?

1300
01:32:44,600 --> 01:32:46,200
Come on, now.

1301
01:32:47,400 --> 01:32:48,900
Talk to me.

1302
01:32:49,600 --> 01:32:50,800
Lena.

1303
01:32:56,000 --> 01:32:59,400
There's only one way to break the curse.

1304
01:33:00,500 --> 01:33:04,100
Genevieve used the Forbidden Spell...

1305
01:33:04,800 --> 01:33:08,200
...to give life to the one she loved.

1306
01:33:08,900 --> 01:33:14,100
To break the curse,
the one that I love has to die.

1307
01:33:14,700 --> 01:33:16,600
Oh, God.

1308
01:33:18,300 --> 01:33:20,300
What are you gonna do?

1309
01:33:24,200 --> 01:33:26,400
I won't hurt Ethan.

1310
01:33:26,900 --> 01:33:28,500
Never.

1311
01:33:30,500 --> 01:33:32,700
They're only our words, Amma.

1312
01:33:33,200 --> 01:33:36,200
They can't explain everything.

1313
01:33:36,800 --> 01:33:41,500
There are all kinds of ways
someone you love can die.

1314
01:33:43,600 --> 01:33:45,600
ETHAN: - That's all the book said?
LENA: - Yeah.

1315
01:33:45,800 --> 01:33:49,600
All it said was to reverse the curse,
I need to do these certain rituals...

1316
01:33:49,800 --> 01:33:53,400
...Caster stuff, every night and every day
right up until the Claiming.

1317
01:33:53,600 --> 01:33:56,000
- And whatever happens, happens.
ETHAN: - Hey.

1318
01:33:56,200 --> 01:33:58,500
We know what's gonna happen.

1319
01:33:58,900 --> 01:34:00,900
I want you to do something for me.

1320
01:34:01,000 --> 01:34:04,300
Between now and my birthday,
I don't want to think about the Claiming.

1321
01:34:04,400 --> 01:34:06,400
See? No tattoo.

1322
01:34:06,900 --> 01:34:10,900
I just want to be with you
and do normal boyfriend-girlfriend stuff.

1323
01:34:11,100 --> 01:34:12,100
- Great.
- Heh.

1324
01:34:12,300 --> 01:34:15,900
Well, how about tonight
is, uh, the Christmas dance and...

1325
01:34:16,100 --> 01:34:17,700
...you could be my date.

1326
01:34:17,900 --> 01:34:22,100
Is Ethan Wate asking me to the dance?
Oh, my God.

1327
01:34:22,300 --> 01:34:23,300
I'm thinking about it.

1328
01:34:23,500 --> 01:34:25,300
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1329
01:34:25,400 --> 01:34:29,400
No, they've got piss punch and the chaperones
guarding the make-out stairs.

1330
01:34:29,600 --> 01:34:32,500
- Heh.
- It is God-awful. Heh.

1331
01:34:32,700 --> 01:34:34,800
Sounds perfect.

1332
01:34:40,200 --> 01:34:43,000
- I still don't know what to get you.
- Huh?

1333
01:34:43,200 --> 01:34:45,700
I mean, we don't celebrate Christmas.

1334
01:34:45,800 --> 01:34:47,200
Oh.

1335
01:34:48,800 --> 01:34:52,900
What do you wish for every year
that you never get?

1336
01:34:56,100 --> 01:34:57,700
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1337
01:34:59,400 --> 01:35:00,700
Oh, well, no.

1338
01:35:00,900 --> 01:35:01,900
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1339
01:35:02,100 --> 01:35:04,400
No, it's not... You're gonna think
I'm so not cool.

1340
01:35:04,600 --> 01:35:06,900
LENA;
That's okay, I don't think you're cool now.

1341
01:35:07,100 --> 01:35:08,500
(ETHAN CHUCKLES)

1342
01:35:10,700 --> 01:35:12,700
Um...

1343
01:35:16,600 --> 01:35:18,200
Snow.

1344
01:35:19,300 --> 01:35:21,100
- Really?
- Ha, ha, yeah.

1345
01:35:21,300 --> 01:35:26,200
Well, you know what, I always wanted
one of those white movie Christmases.

1346
01:35:26,400 --> 01:35:30,100
I mean, look at this. This is,
like, pathetic. This ain't Christmas, heh.

1347
01:35:30,300 --> 01:35:34,000
- You know that set-up's too easy.
- Yeah, I know.

1348
01:35:35,100 --> 01:35:37,300
That's what you really want?

1349
01:35:59,200 --> 01:36:02,500
How am I gonna survive a lifetime
of you surprising me?

1350
01:36:02,700 --> 01:36:04,000
(LENA CHUCKLES)

1351
01:36:18,300 --> 01:36:20,400
Hear how quiet it is?

1352
01:36:31,600 --> 01:36:34,100
LENA: (THINKING) <i>Goodbye, Ethan.</i>

1353
01:36:47,500 --> 01:36:49,100
(DOOR CLOSES)

1354
01:36:49,600 --> 01:36:51,200
AMMA: Ethan?

1355
01:36:54,100 --> 01:36:55,900
Ethan!

1356
01:36:58,900 --> 01:37:00,900
Did you come home late
from the dance last night?

1357
01:37:01,100 --> 01:37:02,100
ETHAN: Um...

1358
01:37:02,300 --> 01:37:04,200
Can you get this turkey
out of the refrigerator?

1359
01:37:04,300 --> 01:37:05,500
Yeah.

1360
01:37:05,700 --> 01:37:10,600
I don't, uh... I don't remember.
I must have been pretty tired.

1361
01:37:10,800 --> 01:37:13,600
But I slept real good
for the first time in a long time.

1362
01:37:13,800 --> 01:37:15,300
Oh, that's good.

1363
01:37:15,400 --> 01:37:18,200
Lena coming over for Christmas?
We got enough food.

1364
01:37:18,400 --> 01:37:19,900
Lena?

1365
01:37:20,800 --> 01:37:22,200
Lena Duchannes.

1366
01:37:22,800 --> 01:37:25,900
Lena Duchannes? Why would I invite
Lena Duchannes over for dinner?

1367
01:37:26,000 --> 01:37:27,100
I barely know her.

1368
01:37:27,200 --> 01:37:30,300
She doesn't speak to anybody at school.
Do you know her?

1369
01:37:35,400 --> 01:37:37,800
Emily's mom says
she was in a mental institution.

1370
01:37:37,900 --> 01:37:42,200
I don't know whether I trust what Emily's
mom says, but she's kind of a weird girl.

1371
01:37:42,400 --> 01:37:44,600
Except for that damn
Civil War thing and meals...

1372
01:37:44,800 --> 01:37:48,400
...I'm staying in my bed
the entire winter break.

1373
01:37:55,900 --> 01:37:58,100
STEPHENS: <i>I don't want to preach today.</i>

1374
01:37:59,000 --> 01:38:02,900
<i>Instead, I just want to talk to you.</i>

1375
01:38:03,800 --> 01:38:06,700
About a word we don't hear much anymore:

1376
01:38:07,600 --> 01:38:09,500
Sacrifice.

1377
01:38:10,600 --> 01:38:13,300
It's not what I'd call a modern word.

1378
01:38:13,500 --> 01:38:16,500
People hear the word "sacrifice"
and they become afraid...

1379
01:38:16,700 --> 01:38:19,500
...that something
will be taken away from them.

1380
01:38:19,600 --> 01:38:23,000
Or they'll have to give up something
they can't live without.

1381
01:38:23,700 --> 01:38:27,100
"Sacrifice," to them, means "loss"...

1382
01:38:27,200 --> 01:38:30,500
...in a world telling us we can have it all.

1383
01:38:32,000 --> 01:38:36,500
But I believe true sacrifice is a victory.

1384
01:38:36,600 --> 01:38:39,800
Because it requires our free will...

1385
01:38:40,000 --> 01:38:43,200
...to give up something
or someone you love...

1386
01:38:43,800 --> 01:38:48,100
...for something or someone
you love more than yourself.

1387
01:38:49,800 --> 01:38:50,800
I won't lie to you.

1388
01:38:51,900 --> 01:38:53,700
<i>It's a gamble.</i>

1389
01:38:54,200 --> 01:38:57,100
<i>Sacrifice won't take away the pain of loss.</i>

1390
01:38:57,200 --> 01:38:59,900
<i>But it wins the battle against bitterness.</i>

1391
01:39:00,100 --> 01:39:05,800
<i>The bitterness that dims the light
on all that is of true value in our lives.</i>

1392
01:39:41,700 --> 01:39:45,000
RIDLEY: <i>What do we do now, Auntie Sarafine?
She gave him up.</i>

1393
01:39:45,200 --> 01:39:49,100
SARAFINE: <i>
She loves that boy. The curse will still work.</i>

1394
01:39:49,300 --> 01:39:51,000
<i>But we'll need his friend.</i>

1395
01:39:51,200 --> 01:39:55,700
RIDLEY: <i>Oh, my sugar darling?
He's ready to go whenever I call.</i>

1396
01:39:56,700 --> 01:39:58,500
Can I do it again?

1397
01:39:59,000 --> 01:40:03,000
You can't tell anyone.
Promise me you won't tell a living soul?

1398
01:40:03,200 --> 01:40:05,700
I won't, I swear it.

1399
01:40:06,500 --> 01:40:10,600
Okay, one last time. Try it again.

1400
01:40:15,800 --> 01:40:17,400
LINK: That is so cool.

1401
01:40:18,300 --> 01:40:22,000
I'll let you know when to do it, sugar.
You'll hear me loud and clear.

1402
01:40:22,100 --> 01:40:24,400
Just like you always do.

1403
01:40:25,100 --> 01:40:29,200
You have no idea how much
I just love you to death right now.

1404
01:40:41,400 --> 01:40:43,300
(CHATTERING)

1405
01:40:54,900 --> 01:40:56,900
OFFICER: Ready? Fire!

1406
01:40:57,000 --> 01:40:58,500
Fire!

1407
01:41:09,000 --> 01:41:10,600
Awesome.

1408
01:41:20,600 --> 01:41:21,700
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

1409
01:41:22,800 --> 01:41:24,300
Come in.

1410
01:41:29,100 --> 01:41:31,700
Are you ready to get dressed?

1411
01:41:32,300 --> 01:41:34,300
It's real pretty.

1412
01:41:42,800 --> 01:41:45,200
You've done the right thing.

1413
01:41:45,300 --> 01:41:47,500
How will I know if it worked?

1414
01:41:47,700 --> 01:41:51,900
When the curse has been paid, you'll feel it.

1415
01:41:52,300 --> 01:41:54,100
You'll know.

1416
01:41:55,200 --> 01:42:00,300
Oh, people are starting to arrive,
sweetheart. It's time.

1417
01:42:02,800 --> 01:42:06,400
Mavis, you look very special.

1418
01:42:06,600 --> 01:42:11,000
Well, heh, it is a very special day.

1419
01:42:20,400 --> 01:42:22,100
- Mom?
- Hi, sugar.

1420
01:42:22,300 --> 01:42:26,200
MR. LEE: Careful with that. Just because
there's no bullet don't mean it can't burn you.

1421
01:42:26,600 --> 01:42:30,600
You're both late. Take a rifle and load.
You two are going to Greenbrier.

1422
01:42:33,500 --> 01:42:36,400
DEL: Urn, hello, everyone. And, uh...

1423
01:42:37,200 --> 01:42:40,400
Oh, thank you for coming. Um...

1424
01:42:40,600 --> 01:42:45,000
The moon will be out soon,
so we should... Uh, we should start.

1425
01:42:45,200 --> 01:42:46,800
(CLEARS THROAT)

1426
01:42:48,000 --> 01:42:49,800
Urn, phew, heh.

1427
01:42:50,000 --> 01:42:54,500
Excuse me. As the Ancients have foretold...

1428
01:42:55,300 --> 01:42:58,200
<i>...a Natural will be Claimed.</i>

1429
01:42:58,800 --> 01:43:02,600
<i>For it has been predetermined
by the five elements...</i>

1430
01:43:02,800 --> 01:43:05,000
<i>...that upon this night...</i>

1431
01:43:05,200 --> 01:43:08,900
<i>...an old cycle shall end
and a new cycle shall begin...</i>

1432
01:43:09,100 --> 01:43:12,000
<i>...wherein the powers of Light and Dark
will merge...</i>

1433
01:43:12,200 --> 01:43:14,300
<i>...and that upon this child...</i>

1434
01:43:14,500 --> 01:43:16,800
...who becomes a woman...

1435
01:43:17,000 --> 01:43:18,500
...Lena Duchannes...

1436
01:43:18,700 --> 01:43:24,800
...her true nature will reveal
the true nature of all power...

1437
01:43:24,900 --> 01:43:26,000
<i>...for the new cycle.</i>

1438
01:43:26,100 --> 01:43:28,100
(HUMMING)

1439
01:43:40,300 --> 01:43:41,500
Hey, halt!

1440
01:43:42,300 --> 01:43:47,400
Or shoot me. I'm so goddamn itchy,
I swear, I'd just rather be a casualty.

1441
01:43:47,600 --> 01:43:51,000
This is so stupid. I wish I was, ugh...

1442
01:43:51,200 --> 01:43:53,000
You want to just kill each other?

1443
01:43:53,600 --> 01:43:56,900
- Come over, watch a movie?
- Aliens? Blu-ray?

1444
01:43:57,000 --> 01:44:00,400
All right. On the count of three.

1445
01:44:03,600 --> 01:44:05,000
