01:46:54,000 --> 01:46:56,300
MACON: Lena, stop.

1476
01:47:03,800 --> 01:47:05,500
Macon?

1477
01:47:07,500 --> 01:47:10,300
MACON: Stop this, please.

1478
01:47:11,200 --> 01:47:14,400
Macon. Macon, what have you done?

1479
01:47:15,100 --> 01:47:19,400
The curse had to be paid.

1480
01:47:20,400 --> 01:47:21,700
I don't understand.

1481
01:47:21,900 --> 01:47:25,500
Somebody you love has to die.

1482
01:47:26,500 --> 01:47:30,000
That was a sneaky trick, Macon. No fair.

1483
01:47:32,000 --> 01:47:33,500
Macon?

1484
01:47:33,600 --> 01:47:36,400
I promised his mother.

1485
01:47:37,500 --> 01:47:39,700
I can't lose you.

1486
01:47:40,600 --> 01:47:43,900
- It's all right, it's all right, Lena.
- No.

1487
01:47:45,300 --> 01:47:47,800
Don't let them fool you.

1488
01:47:48,800 --> 01:47:50,600
Claim...

1489
01:47:51,700 --> 01:47:54,000
...yourself.

1490
01:48:02,900 --> 01:48:04,800
(CRYING)

1491
01:48:04,900 --> 01:48:06,300
LENA: No.

1492
01:48:18,500 --> 01:48:20,300
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1493
01:48:25,500 --> 01:48:26,600
Uh-oh.

1494
01:48:30,200 --> 01:48:31,300
What are you doing?

1495
01:48:31,400 --> 01:48:34,300
I think this is just between
you and me, Mama.

1496
01:48:34,500 --> 01:48:36,100
Fine with me.

1497
01:48:36,800 --> 01:48:40,900
Ridley, don't be afraid. She's on our side.

1498
01:48:41,000 --> 01:48:43,500
She's our Lena. You listen to me.

1499
01:48:43,700 --> 01:48:47,500
You're my daughter. I always wanted you
with me. They took you from me.

1500
01:48:47,700 --> 01:48:51,800
The moon appears, and it will claim you
as you are destined to be claimed.

1501
01:48:52,000 --> 01:48:55,400
Accept it, sweetheart.
There's nothing you can do.

1502
01:49:06,000 --> 01:49:07,200
(CHUCKLES)

1503
01:49:09,500 --> 01:49:10,800
No one can do that.

1504
01:49:11,500 --> 01:49:14,900
Let me go! She's more powerful than you.

1505
01:49:15,000 --> 01:49:17,600
Lena. Lena, listen to me.

1506
01:49:17,800 --> 01:49:20,000
It was her idea.

1507
01:49:20,100 --> 01:49:23,600
She told me you were going Dark anyway.
I would never hurt you.

1508
01:49:23,800 --> 01:49:26,800
You remember when I left,
so I wouldn't hurt you?

1509
01:49:27,200 --> 01:49:28,300
Lena?

1510
01:49:28,400 --> 01:49:30,300
Go.

1511
01:49:32,700 --> 01:49:34,600
Thanks, coz.

1512
01:49:38,000 --> 01:49:39,200
(CHUCKLES)

1513
01:49:40,900 --> 01:49:43,700
You know, you're a lot more like me
than you care to admit.

1514
01:49:43,900 --> 01:49:45,500
Well, nobody's perfect.

1515
01:49:45,600 --> 01:49:49,700
Lena, you have great powers.
I can teach you how to use them.

1516
01:49:49,800 --> 01:49:53,400
I can teach you how to become
the most powerful Dark Caster who ever lived.

1517
01:49:53,600 --> 01:49:55,500
Oh, that's so sweet of you, Mama.

1518
01:49:55,700 --> 01:50:00,200
Oh, baby. This mortal you think you love?
You can never be together.

1519
01:50:00,300 --> 01:50:01,600
I know.

1520
01:50:01,800 --> 01:50:03,800
Did you ever love me, Mama?

1521
01:50:04,000 --> 01:50:06,100
(CHUCKLES)

1522
01:50:08,300 --> 01:50:10,500
You know, I don't remember.

1523
01:50:10,600 --> 01:50:13,000
No mother does, really.

1524
01:50:13,200 --> 01:50:16,500
It's not easy, you know,
pushing another female out of your body...

1525
01:50:16,600 --> 01:50:21,700
...a younger, more perfect version of yourself,
with every option and no mistakes, heh.

1526
01:50:21,900 --> 01:50:24,000
Anyhow, love is a trick of the mind,
you know?

1527
01:50:24,200 --> 01:50:28,200
It doesn't really exist.
There's no such thing in nature.

1528
01:50:28,800 --> 01:50:31,400
Love's a spell, created by mortals...

1529
01:50:31,600 --> 01:50:35,400
...to give their females something to play with
instead of power.

1530
01:50:35,500 --> 01:50:38,300
I want you to have power.

1531
01:50:38,600 --> 01:50:41,100
I want you to be who you truly are.

1532
01:50:41,200 --> 01:50:43,500
As long as I'm just like you.

1533
01:50:44,100 --> 01:50:46,500
There's Darkness in you.
Don't you try and deny it.

1534
01:50:46,600 --> 01:50:48,000
I don't.

1535
01:50:48,100 --> 01:50:51,100
Well, then claim it. Claim it
and come with me, be with me.

1536
01:50:51,300 --> 01:50:54,900
We can rule over a new world, our world.

1537
01:50:57,400 --> 01:50:59,400
(GRUNTS)

1538
01:50:59,900 --> 01:51:01,200
(GASPING)

1539
01:51:01,400 --> 01:51:03,200
What are you doing?

1540
01:51:03,800 --> 01:51:06,000
It is a new world, Mama.

1541
01:51:06,100 --> 01:51:09,600
But it ain't all Dark, and it ain't all Light.

1542
01:51:09,800 --> 01:51:11,500
And it ain't all ours.

1543
01:51:17,200 --> 01:51:19,800
I remember now. I remember now,
I did love you.

1544
01:51:20,000 --> 01:51:22,300
I do love you. I love you, darling. I love you!

1545
01:51:22,500 --> 01:51:25,700
You really shouldn't use words
you don't understand.

1546
01:51:28,700 --> 01:51:31,300
You still need me!

1547
01:51:31,500 --> 01:51:33,000
You've done enough, Mama.

1548
01:51:36,200 --> 01:51:40,200
You must be Claimed!

1549
01:51:42,500 --> 01:51:43,600
(SCREAMING)

1550
01:52:08,800 --> 01:52:10,300
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1551
01:52:13,100 --> 01:52:14,200
Macon?

1552
01:52:19,800 --> 01:52:21,600
You all right, coz?

1553
01:52:22,800 --> 01:52:24,100
Yeah.

1554
01:52:28,800 --> 01:52:32,600
Macon said this was the only way
to protect you both.

1555
01:52:42,200 --> 01:52:43,600
(LENA SOBBING)

1556
01:52:43,700 --> 01:52:48,700
LENA: <i>I could hear the sound.
The sound was me breaking.</i>

1557
01:52:49,600 --> 01:52:52,200
<i>I cried because he had lived.</i>

1558
01:52:52,400 --> 01:52:54,900
<i>Because he had died.</i>

1559
01:52:55,300 --> 01:52:59,300
<i>I was shattered, I was saved.</i>

1560
01:52:59,600 --> 01:53:02,700
<i>I only knew the girl I was, was gone.</i>

1561
01:53:03,800 --> 01:53:08,800
<i>He was right. No good can come
from loving a mortal.</i>

1562
01:53:09,800 --> 01:53:12,800
<i>They can't survive our world.</i>

1563
01:53:14,700 --> 01:53:16,500
<i>Get out. Go, Ethan.</i>

1564
01:53:17,800 --> 01:53:21,100
<i>Claim yourself in defiance...</i>

1565
01:53:21,200 --> 01:53:25,600
<i>...in hope, in love, in fury, in gratitude.</i>

1566
01:53:25,800 --> 01:53:29,200
<i>Claim the Light. Claim the Dark.</i>

1567
01:53:29,300 --> 01:53:30,900
<i>Claim it all.</i>

1568
01:53:31,900 --> 01:53:34,000
<i>Nothing can stay.</i>

1569
01:53:40,900 --> 01:53:42,400
- You all set?
ETHAN: - Yeah.

1570
01:53:42,600 --> 01:53:45,200
Should be in New York
by Thursday if we make good time.

1571
01:53:45,300 --> 01:53:47,700
We're gonna go stay
with Link's cousin in Brooklyn.

1572
01:53:47,900 --> 01:53:49,300
AMMA: Come here.

1573
01:53:49,500 --> 01:53:51,400
ETHAN: I'll call you as soon as I get in.

1574
01:53:52,200 --> 01:53:54,400
You call whenever you can.

1575
01:53:54,500 --> 01:53:56,000
Bye.

1576
01:54:02,000 --> 01:54:03,600
Hi, um...

1577
01:54:03,700 --> 01:54:05,400
- Lena, right?
- Hi, yeah.

1578
01:54:05,500 --> 01:54:07,700
- Ethan Wate.
- Yeah, I know.

1579
01:54:07,900 --> 01:54:09,900
Oh. Heh, um...

1580
01:54:12,000 --> 01:54:14,100
So I wanted, I... You know...

1581
01:54:14,200 --> 01:54:16,100
Um...

1582
01:54:16,300 --> 01:54:20,700
I'm sorry that we never got to hang,
but I always wanted to tell you...

1583
01:54:20,800 --> 01:54:25,300
...I thought your, uh, poems
in Creative Writing...

1584
01:54:25,800 --> 01:54:27,500
...just really good.

1585
01:54:28,800 --> 01:54:31,900
Thanks. That's really nice of you to say.

1586
01:54:35,100 --> 01:54:37,700
- You're leaving?
- Yeah, uh...

1587
01:54:37,900 --> 01:54:40,200
College road trip, heh.

1588
01:54:40,300 --> 01:54:42,700
I'm going to check out NYU.

1589
01:54:42,800 --> 01:54:45,200
Great. It's good.

1590
01:54:51,400 --> 01:54:53,000
Oh, cool title.

1591
01:54:53,700 --> 01:54:55,600
Bukowski?

1592
01:54:56,100 --> 01:54:57,800
He any good?

1593
01:54:59,400 --> 01:55:01,000
Define "good."

1594
01:55:02,800 --> 01:55:05,500
(CHUCKLING)

1595
01:55:08,300 --> 01:55:12,300
Keep it. A "Getting Outta Gatlin" present.

1596
01:55:14,000 --> 01:55:15,400
Really?

1597
01:55:16,400 --> 01:55:18,900
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1598
01:55:23,800 --> 01:55:25,300
Cool. Thank you.

1599
01:55:25,400 --> 01:55:27,400
All right. See you.

1600
01:55:27,500 --> 01:55:29,200
See you.

1601
01:55:35,000 --> 01:55:37,000
Ethan's coming. All right, bye.

1602
01:55:37,200 --> 01:55:38,400
- Hey, is it all right...
- Ah.

1603
01:55:38,500 --> 01:55:41,200
...If we go see my morn at the sanatorium?
It's on the way.

1604
01:55:41,300 --> 01:55:42,400
Sure.

